50|$|<b>A</b> double <b>referendum</b> {{was held}} in Georgia on 5 January 2008 {{alongside}} presidential elections. One question was <b>a</b> binding <b>referendum</b> <b>on</b> whether to bring forward the 2008 parliamentary elections from October to April/May. The second was <b>a</b> non-binding advisory <b>referendum</b> <b>on</b> joining NATO. Both proposals were approved with over 75% in favour. Parliamentary elections were subsequently held on 21 May.|$|R
